<h1 class="title style-scope ytd-video-primary-info-renderer">Odd-Eyes Rebellion Dragon - Overlord Deck Odd-Eyes Raging Dragon 2020</h1>

The goal of the deck is to do the standard Mayakashi synchro ladder while also hopefully getting a Balerdroch in the process. Jack A' Booran and Yuki-musume help tie the Zombie World stuff and the Mayakashi stuff together so that it all works out better than you'd expect. Uni-Zombies provide an alternative normal summon to Hajun when you brick as it can potentially help you get a Mayakashi ladder going depending on your opening, or it can allow you to rush for Balerdroch. Thanks to the new Mayakashi link-4 the deck has solid control properties that combined with Balerdroch and Gravity Collapse make for a strong going-first deck (when you don't brick) that can also easily go second and do some unga bunga zombie caveman beatdown. The deck gets absolutely eaten alive by handtraps and disruption in general, so 3 Called By the Grave are mandatory. I opted to include 4 revival traps as they play nicely with the Mayakashi synchros to use their revival effects as quick-effects, but the Buddy Forces are only my personal preference and could very easily be replaced with Ash Blossoms or something else if so desired. Return of the Zombies also makes for solid removal with Zombie World up, and its general utility and re-usability makes it a staple card IMO. The side deck is basically just all staples, really run whatever you want. You could also alternatively play 3x Give and Take in place of Gravity Collapse as they both accomplish similar goals of preventing any fun, but Gravity Collapse is generally more potent.

&nbsp;

Overall the deck is decently versatile and a lot of fun to play (although admittedly it's kinda annoying in YGOpro because of Dakki). Somewhat weak consistency and a limited extra deck hold back the deck a tad, but Mayakashis have more than enough tools to deal with a wide variety of situations.
